Another rvest exercise - cricbuzz

Something more topical this time. Lets scrape the IPL schedule.

Open this webpage in chrome and see: https://www.cricbuzz.com/cricket-series/2810/indian-premier-league-2019/matches

What all features can we scrape from here?

  • date
  • team A
  • team B
  • venue
  • match#
  • time
  • result
  • etc.

Lets do this.

# setup chunk

suppressPackageStartupMessages({
  
  if (!require(imager)){install.packages("imager")}
  library(imager) 
  library(rvest)
  library(XML)
  library(magrittr)
  library(stringr)

})

url = "https://www.cricbuzz.com/cricket-series/2810/indian-premier-league-2019/matches"
page = url %>% read_html()

Extracting Teams that played

teams.nodes = page %>% html_nodes(".text-hvr-underline span")
xmlTreeParse(teams.nodes[[1]])  # parse one node

Spot what is interesting enough to scrape above.

teams.text = teams.nodes %>% html_text()
teams.text[1:5]   # view a few
## [1] "Chennai Super Kings vs Royal Challengers Bangalore, 1st Match"
## [2] "Kolkata Knight Riders vs Sunrisers Hyderabad, 2nd Match"      
## [3] "Mumbai Indians vs Delhi Capitals, 3rd Match"                  
## [4] "Rajasthan Royals vs Kings XI Punjab, 4th Match"               
## [5] "Delhi Capitals vs Chennai Super Kings, 5th Match"

Clearly, lotsa refining needed.

# get teams A, B and matchNum
a0 = str_split(teams.text, " vs ") %>% unlist()

teamA_seq = seq(from=1, to=length(a0), by=2)  # try ?seq

teamA = a0[teamA_seq]
teamA[1:5]
## [1] "Chennai Super Kings"   "Kolkata Knight Riders" "Mumbai Indians"       
## [4] "Rajasthan Royals"      "Delhi Capitals"
teamB_seq = seq(from=2, to=length(teams.text), by=2)
teamB = a0[teamB_seq]
teamB[1:5]
## [1] "Royal Challengers Bangalore, 1st Match"
## [2] "Sunrisers Hyderabad, 2nd Match"        
## [3] "Delhi Capitals, 3rd Match"             
## [4] "Kings XI Punjab, 4th Match"            
## [5] "Chennai Super Kings, 5th Match"

Uh-oh. More processing needed.

# more processing needed
teamB1 = teamB %>% str_split(",") %>% unlist()
teamB1[1:5]
## [1] "Royal Challengers Bangalore" " 1st Match"                 
## [3] "Sunrisers Hyderabad"         " 2nd Match"                 
## [5] "Delhi Capitals"
teamB_seq = seq(from=1, to=length(teamB1), by=2)
teamB = teamB1[teamB_seq]
teamB[1:5]
## [1] "Royal Challengers Bangalore" "Sunrisers Hyderabad"        
## [3] "Delhi Capitals"              "Kings XI Punjab"            
## [5] "Chennai Super Kings"

Finally, lets not forget match number.

matchNum_seq = seq(from=2, to=length(teamB1), by=2)
matchNum = teamB1[matchNum_seq]
matchNum[1:5]
## [1] " 1st Match" " 2nd Match" " 3rd Match" " 4th Match" " 5th Match"

Look through SelectorGadget again and ID the tags we need to scrape venue and time pls.

# getting venue and time
venues = page %>% html_nodes(".cb-col-60 .text-gray") %>% html_text()
times = page %>% html_nodes(".text-gray span+ span") %>% html_text()

venues[1:5]
## [1] "MA Chidambaram Stadium, Chennai" "Eden Gardens, Kolkata"          
## [3] "Wankhede Stadium, Mumbai"        "Sawai Mansingh Stadium, Jaipur" 
## [5] "Feroz Shah Kotla, Delhi"
times[1:5]
## [1] " 08:00 PM" " 04:00 PM" " 08:00 PM" " 08:00 PM" " 08:00 PM"

Above can be bound into a neat DF. Results below are partial since many matches are yet to be played.

# getting results
results = page %>% html_nodes(".cb-text-complete") %>% html_text()
tail(results)
## [1] "Kolkata Knight Riders won by 8 wkts"
## [2] "Kings XI Punjab won by 6 wkts"      
## [3] "Chennai Super Kings won by 7 wkts"

Last but not least, scraping images off of cricbuzz.

Scrapiing images

# scraping images off of cricbuzz

url1 = "https://www.cricbuzz.com/cricket-series/2810/indian-premier-league-2019/photos"
page1 = url1 %>% read_html()

img.urls1  = page1 %>% html_nodes(".cb-lst-img") %>% html_attr("src")
img.urls = paste0("https://www.cricbuzz.com",img.urls1)
head(img.urls)
## [1] "https://www.cricbuzz.com/a/img/v1/100x77/i1/c167847/ipl-2019-rr-vs-csk.jpg"          
## [2] "https://www.cricbuzz.com/a/img/v1/100x77/i1/c167820/mi-vs-kxip-match-24-ipl-2019.jpg"
## [3] "https://www.cricbuzz.com/a/img/v1/100x77/i1/c167757/csk-vs-kkr-match-23-ipl-2019.jpg"
## [4] "https://www.cricbuzz.com/a/img/v1/100x77/i1/c167709/kxip-vs-srh-match-22-ipl-201.jpg"
## [5] "https://www.cricbuzz.com/a/img/v1/100x77/i1/c167656/ipl-2019-rajasthan-royals-vs.jpg"
download.file(img.urls[1], 'x.jpg', mode='wb')

Look in the Files list, the image should have come.

Last but not least, will use imager to display the image thus stored.

require(imager)
load.image("./x.jpg") %>% plot()
